  - `reader_user_id` (UUID) 
  - `session_id` (String, max 255)
  - `read_at` (Instant, auto-set to now)

#### **3. Status Computation Logic (MessagingService.java, lines 353-361)**
```java
private MessageResponse toMessageResponse(Message m, UUID viewerId, Map<UUID, Long> readCounts) {
    String status = null;
    if (m.getSender() != null && m.getSender().getId().equals(viewerId)) {
        status = readCounts.getOrDefault(m.getId(), 0L) > 0 ? "READ" : "SENT";
    }
    return MessageResponse.from(m, IMG_BASE, status, ...);
}
```

This relies on `readCounts` map populated by:
```java
Map<UUID, Long> counts = new HashMap<>();
for (Object[] row : receiptRepo.countReadsByMessageExcludingSender(myIds, viewerId)) {
    counts.put((UUID) row[0], (Long) row[1]);  // messageId -> count of distinct readers
}
```

